p_rec.organization = o_rec
p_rec.description = 'The City of Oakland\'s Housing Assistance Center offers a streamlined, one-stop approach for obtaining housing services and resource referrals by Oakland residents, homeowners, and property owners and managers.	HOUSING ASSISTANCE RESOURCES:	A trained Housing Intake Specialist supports clients in finding and securing safe and affordable housing; 	- Places clients in emergency and transitional housing;	- Connects clients with City, County, nonprofit, private, and other public housing related resources; and 	- Provides referrals for tenants and landlords. 	- A Community Housing Advocate helps Center clients navigate access to housing services and serves as an advocate in obtaining those services;	- Assists clients in accessing resources for rent, deposits, home repairs and other housing needs; and	- Works with County and City specialists to alleviate complex housing needs.	STREAMLINED ACCESS TO CITY HOUSING SERVICES, INCLUDING:	- Tenant petitions and landlord/tenant mediation for rent increases and related rent adjustment issues.	- Low-or no-interest loans and grants for residential rehabilitation, home repairs and energy retrofits for eligible residents.	- Foreclosure prevention and mitigation assistance for homeowners, including housing counseling and referrals for legal services.	- Information about first-time homebuyers\' assistance and workshops.'
