p_rec = Program.find_or_create_by title: 'Access Hayward', organization: o_rec, is_official: true
p_rec.organization = o_rec
p_rec.description = 'Hayward City Hall is now accessible 24/7 - Online and by Telephone. Access Hayward is a customer service system that creates a virtual City Hall, which now enables residents, businesses, and anyone else seeking information or services from the City, to do so when it is most convenient for them - around the clock. The system automatically sends inquiries and service requests to the right City official to follow-up within prescribed timelines. It also automatically provides a status update through email or by telephone to the party requesting assistance. Each inquiry is provided a case number, so those wishing to initiate a status update on a request may do so as well.	ACCESS HAYWARD is easy to use. One simply needs to go online to the City of Hayward website: www.hayward-ca.gov and click on the ACCESS HAYWARD logo. User friendly guidelines help lead the way to getting needed information or services. For those who do not have access to the internet, or who simply are not comfortable using the computer, can also access the system by telephone by dialing: 1-510 -HAYWARD  (or 1-510-429-9273). From street and sidewalk repairs, to reporting graffiti, traffic concerns, and barking dogs, to obtaining official documents or learning about available services, and more â€“ information and service in Hayward is now just a click or telephone call away.'
