p_rec = Program.find_or_create_by title: 'Paratransit Program (ADA Paratransit Service)', organization: o_rec, is_official: true
p_rec.organization = o_rec
p_rec.description = 'East Bay Paratransit is only available to people who are prevented by a disability from using the regular transit of systems such as AC Transit or BART without the aid of another person. Regulations for eligibility come from the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA). 	Service is provided during the hours of AC Transit\'s bus and BART\'s rail operations. Service is limited to areas within 3/4 mile of an operating bus route or BART station.	ELIGIBILITY: Full or limited eligibility is assigned for a period of three years. Reapplication every three years is required for continuous service. Temporary eligibility is assigned for a limited time for those whose disability or health is expected to improve. Eligibility Certification hours are Monday-Friday, 8-5.	RESERVATIONS: Travel is arranged only through advance phone reservation. Reservation hours are 8-5 daily, including weekends. Reservations can be made as early as seven days in advance, and must be made no later than 5pm the day before the trip.	TO PURCHASE TICKETS:  Tickets may be purchased in person or by mail from: East Bay Paratransit 1722 Broadway, 1st floor, Oakland, 94612 (Monday-Friday, 8-5). Call Paratransit office or go to website for additional ticket sale locations countywide. Tickets are available in $1 or $4 denominations, sold in books of 10, and do not expire. To purchase tickets by mail, postage and handling fees apply.	ADDITIONAL SERVICES PHONE HOURS: Administration: Monday-Friday, 8-5; Cancellations: 24 hours daily; Complaints: 24 hours daily; Customer Service: 4am-1am daily; General Information: 4am-1am daily.'
