p_rec.description = 'Supplemental Security Income (SSI) is a federally funded program providing benefits for people with specific physical or psychological impairments. SSI applies if impairments disable a client for 12 or more months or will likely result in death.	Provides social worker assistance throughout the entire SSI application and appeal process. Assistance includes: seeing that the case is properly evaluated according to state regulations; obtaining the necessary documents for the case or arranging for medical and psychological tests as needed; helping with transportation to and from appointments; working with the Social Security Administration and the Adult Disability Division of the California State Office of Social Services to make sure all requirements for applying for SSI are met; working closely with other community organizations and Health Care Providers to help clients get the services needed.'
